{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set v = card_data.visual %}
{% set band = card_data.band %}
{% set op = card_data.operating %}
{% set fs = card_data.factor_share %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/m1.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="m1-intro">
  <p class="m1-headline">
    One synthetic <strong>{{ card_data.meta.manager_name }}</strong> (equity market-neutral,
    stated net-beta band {{ "%+.2f"|format(band.lower) }} &hellip; {{ "%+.2f"|format(band.upper) }},
    {{ card_data.meta.months }} months). The <strong>measured</strong> net market beta walks out of
    the band; the alarm is a <em>calibrated rule</em>, not a bare breach &mdash; its threshold is set
    on the simulator's autocorrelated honest-wander null.
  </p>
  <span class="tier-badge" data-tier="E">E &middot; measured</span>
</section>

<aside class="m1-guide" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2 class="m1-panel__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div class="m1-guide__block">
    <h3 class="m1-guide__subtitle">What you are looking at</h3>
    <p class="m1-note">
      A synthetic {{ card_data.meta.manager_name }} book whose stated net-beta band is
      {{ "%+.2f"|format(band.lower) }} &hellip; {{ "%+.2f"|format(band.upper) }} but whose
      <strong>measured</strong> net beta walks out of that band over {{ card_data.meta.months }} months.
      The cumulative-sum alarm holds until the excursion has <em>persisted</em>, then fires at
      month {{ v.alarm_month }} (the drift began at month {{ v.drift_onset }}). Reading the same walk
      from returns instead of exposures, the picture inverts: the measured (E) tier detects it
      {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.rate * 100) }}% of the time by T={{ op.detection_window }} while
      the returns-inferred (R) tier detects it {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_r.rate * 100) }}%.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="m1-guide__block">
    <h3 class="m1-guide__subtitle">How to read it</h3>
    <ul class="m1-guide__list">
      <li><strong>The accent path</strong> is the measured net beta &mdash; disclosed, exact, not inferred.</li>
      <li><strong>The dashed band</strong> is the stated mandate limit; <strong>the shaded envelope</strong>
        is where a non-drifting book of this type wanders (5&ndash;95th percentile of the calibrated null).</li>
      <li><strong>The alarm marker</strong> is where the CUSUM crosses its calibrated threshold; the gap back
        to the drift onset is the honest <em>detection delay</em>.</li>
      <li><strong>The tier badge</strong> marks the panel as measurement (E); <strong>the greyed R chart and
        its noise chip</strong> mark returns-inferred drift that does not clear at this track length.</li>
      <li><strong>The interval bars</strong> are the E and R detection rates and the factor-share slope, each
        with its 95% interval &mdash; never a bare number.</li>
      <li><strong>The power gate</strong> states the calibration: the false-alarm budget the threshold was set
        to, and whether detection cleared the floor that lets the alarm render.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="m1-note">
      This calibrated synthetic path demonstrates the monitoring mechanism, its directional
      sensitivity, and its refusal behavior under known truth. It does not establish drift
      prevalence, external calibration, predictive accuracy, or drift in any live manager.
      The full methodology &mdash; with the math and a reference implementation &mdash; is in the
      <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">method spec</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</aside>

<section class="m1-panel">
  <h2 class="m1-panel__title">The measured net-beta walk &amp; the CUSUM alarm</h2>
  <p class="m1-note">
    The measured path (exact, Robust) against its stated band and the honest-wander null envelope
    (5&ndash;95th percentile). The one-sided CUSUM accumulates sustained excursions beyond the band
    edge and fires at the <strong>onset of the sustained breach</strong> &mdash; a single month over
    the edge does not accumulate to the threshold.
    {% if v.alarm_month is not none %}Alarm fires at month {{ v.alarm_month }} (drift onset {{ v.drift_onset }}).{% endif %}
  </p>
  <svg class="m1-drift-chart" viewBox="0 0 100 44" preserveAspectRatio="none"
       role="img" aria-label="Measured net-beta path against its band, null envelope, and CUSUM alarm onset"></svg>
</section>

<section class="m1-panel">
  <h2 class="m1-panel__title">Tier degradation &mdash; E measures, R only infers</h2>
  <p class="m1-note">
    Identical ground truth, two honesty levels. E reads the disclosed exposure path directly; R infers
    net beta from returns via a {{ card_data.meta.months and "24" }}-month rolling regression (Sharpe 1992).
    At this track length the rolling estimate is too noisy to call the walk &mdash; shown greyed behind a
    noise chip, never a verdict.
  </p>
  <svg class="m1-rbsa-chart" viewBox="0 0 100 30" preserveAspectRatio="none"
       role="img" aria-label="R-tier rolling-beta inference, rendered descriptive-only"></svg>
  <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="noise">returns-inferred &mdash; no drift verdict at this track length</span>
  <div class="m1-detection">
    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="detection"
         data-lo="{{ op.detection_e.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ op.detection_e.rate }}" data-hi="{{ op.detection_e.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">E detection @ T={{ op.detection_window }}</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.rate * 100) }}%</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail"><div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div></div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">Wilson 95% {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.ci_lo * 100) }}% &hellip; {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.ci_hi * 100) }}%{% if op.detection_e.median_delay is not none %}, median delay {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.median_delay) }} mo{% endif %}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="detection"
         data-lo="{{ op.detection_r.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ op.detection_r.rate }}" data-hi="{{ op.detection_r.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">R detection @ T={{ op.detection_window }}</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_r.rate * 100) }}%</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail"><div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div></div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">Wilson 95% {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_r.ci_lo * 100) }}% &hellip; {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_r.ci_hi * 100) }}%</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="m1-panel">
  <h2 class="m1-panel__title">Accidental-factor drift &mdash; factor share of variance</h2>
  <p class="m1-note">
    The factor-explained share of predicted variance over the walk. Estimate-bearing (it uses an
    estimated idiosyncratic variance), so the trend ships as a slope interval with a verdict &mdash;
    never a bare &ldquo;factor share up.&rdquo;
  </p>
  <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="slope"
       data-lo="{{ fs.slope.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ fs.slope.point }}" data-hi="{{ fs.slope.ci_hi }}">
    <span class="interval-stat__label">Factor-share slope (per month)</span>
    <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%+.4f"|format(fs.slope.point) }}</span>
    <div class="interval-stat__rail"><div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div></div>
    <span class="interval-stat__range">95% interval {{ "%+.4f"|format(fs.slope.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%+.4f"|format(fs.slope.ci_hi) }}</span>
  </div>
  <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="{{ 'shrink' if fs.verdict == 'rising' else 'noise' }}">
    {{ 'rising factor share' if fs.verdict == 'rising' else 'no material trend' }}
  </span>
</section>

<section class="m1-panel">
  <h2 class="m1-panel__title">Operating characteristics</h2>
  {% if card_data.alarm_cleared %}
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">power gate &middot; alarm cleared</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">
      Calibrated on {{ op.size_e.n_paths }} honest-wander paths to a
      {{ "%.2f"|format(op.budget_per_year) }}/manager-year false-alarm budget (achieved
      {{ "%.3f"|format(op.size_e.rate) }}); detection of the pinned
      {{ "%.2f"|format(op.pinned_effect) }} net-beta walk is
      {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.rate * 100) }}% by T={{ op.detection_window }} &mdash; above the
      0.50 floor. The alarm is rendered; the R rung is not.
    </p>
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">power gate &middot; demoted to measured-breach flag</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">
      The E-tier CUSUM cannot separate the pinned {{ "%.2f"|format(op.pinned_effect) }} walk from
      honest wander at the budgeted false-alarm rate by T={{ op.detection_window }} (detection
      {{ "%.0f"|format(op.detection_e.rate * 100) }}% &lt; 0.50 floor). Only the instantaneous
      measured-breach flag is shown &mdash; no sustained-drift verdict.
    </p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>The measurement is exact: the breach flag reads the disclosed exposure path against its stated band
with a materiality dead-band, and is Robust by construction. The <em>sustained-drift alarm</em> is a
calibrated rule &mdash; Page's (1954) one-sided CUSUM, whose decision interval <em>h</em> is set on the
simulator's <strong>autocorrelated</strong> honest-wander null (never an iid ARL, which would over-fire
a rotating book). Detection and delay are measured on the drift alternative, each with a Wilson 95%
interval.</p>
<p>The R rung exists only to make the tier degradation visible: returns-based rolling-beta inference at
this track length buries a real net-beta walk in estimation noise &mdash; the do-not-build verdict,
measured, not asserted. The R rung is calibrated with the same allowance as the measured tier; on the
far noisier rolling-beta series no threshold on the calibration grid meets the false-alarm budget
&mdash; the refusal itself is the measured verdict.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/m1-drift.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
